'''Balik''' ({{lang-bg|Балик}}, [[Byzantine Greek]]: {{lang|grc|Μπαλίκας}}; fl. c. 1320 and died 1347) was a noble of the [[Second Bulgarian Empire]] who increased the autonomy of his province and became [[Despot (court title)|despot]] of the [[Principality of Karvuna]]. During the [[Byzantine civil war of 1341–1347]] he supported the regent [[Anna of Savoy]] against pretender [[John VI Kantakouzenos]]. Balik died in 1347, either during an outbreak of the [[Black Death]] or killed during a retaliation campaign led by [[Umur Beg]], on behalf of [[John V Palaiologos]], that destroyed Dobruja's seaports. His brother [[Dobrotitsa]] succeeded him.


